  "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently the Proof-of-Stake downloader (`StartPoSDownloader`, `requestMoreHeadersForPOS`, `ProcessHeadersPOS`, etc in `turbo/stages/headerdownload/header_algos.go`) is too simplistic: it only downloads from one peer at a time, thus making Erigon susceptible to slow or bad peers. That might be a problem during the initial sync, but especially afterwards, at the tip of the chain, CL can occasionally tell Erigon to switch to a side fork with some missing ancestors, and in that scenario the latency of the downloader is crucial.\r\n\r\nFor example, here's the log of an Erigon instance run by gateway.fm, with a few \"[Downloader] Timeout\", leading to erigon failing behind the tip of the chain:\r\n[alloc_logs_erigon.stderr.0.w.log](https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/files/9617406/alloc_logs_erigon.stderr.0.w.log)\r\n\r\nA few things can be made to improve the PoS downloader, namely:\r\n- Simultaneous downloading from multiple peers;\r\n- Better penalization of bad or slow peers;\r\n- Tweaking the number of attempts & timeout threshold.\r\n",
